README v20110803 

  This is the readme file for Mirage project. Mirage is a BSD licensed static
  analyzer tool for security issues.
  
  Starting from the Owasp Orizon concepts, Mirage will fill the gaps using Flex
  && Bison generated parsers to perform static analyisis.

For users
  In order to install mirage and have it running, you have to simply follow the
  standard installation process for GNU tools.

  
For developers who want to hack the code
  1) fork the report from github
  2) launch autoreconf
  3) start hacking 
  4) make me a pull request
  5) Have fun!
  

